      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MINOS NZ (6) has been very good in WA so far, coming from tougher draws to win three of his four starts at this venue and finishing close-up when fourth in stronger company in the other. Had to work last time but toughed it out. Big chance again. PETES HONOUR (5) is in form and hard to knock off a hat-trick wins at this venue, last time overcoming a 40m handicap to get home by 6m. Had to race wide there but was still too good. Big chance again. TUALOU NZ (10) will be fitter for the resuming effort when third from this row. Draws for a trail and could be dangerous if he gets the gaps. THELITTLE MASTER (11) was held up last week but had recorded two wins and a close second from his previous three starts so deserves another chance.",
